              },
              "free_text": [
                " Experiment was performed using the",
                "DRAGON (Detector of Recoils And Gammas Of Nuclear",
                "reactions) recoil separator located at the Isotope",
                "Separator and ACcelerator (ISAC) radioactive beam",
                "facility at the TRIUMF laboratory in Vancouver, Canada."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Windowless gas target was used. The target consisted",
                "of 7.3 - 8.1 mbar of H2 gas with pressures regulated",
                "to 0.04 mbar or better during each hour-long run.",
                "These pressures resulted in energy losses across the",
                "target of 16-20 keV/nucleon."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "BGO"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " target volume was surrounded by 30 bismuth",
                "germanate (BGO) detectors which detected the gamma",
                "rays emitted during the reaction"
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "MAGSP"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Downstream of the target, the reaction",
                "products were separated from the unreacted beam by a",
                "recoil separator consisting of two magnetic (M) and",
                "two electrostatic (E) dipoles, arranged in an MEME",
                "configuration. Charge state, q, selection was",
                "performed after the first magnetic dipole and A/q",
                "selection was performed after the first electrostatic",
                "dipole."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SISD"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The recoils transmitted through the separator",
                "were detected in a double-sided silicon strip",
                "detector (DSSSD)"
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "MCPLT"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Local time-of-flight (TOF) system, consisting",
                "of two microchannel plate (MCP) detectors, was used",
                "to increase the beam suppression through improved",
                "particle identification"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TOF"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Time of flight was used to increase the beam",
                "suppression through improved particle identification"
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "COINC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " coincidence between gamma rays in BGO and",
                "reaction products, detected by Si strip detector was",
                "used to reduce background."
              ]
            }
          ],
